Comments: In legacy NFS environments (NFSv2 and NFSv3), the client relies on the RPC port mapper (rpcbind on port 111) to dynamically discover which ports the mountd, nlockmgr (Network Lock Manager), and status services are using.

NFSv4 was specifically redesigned to be firewall-friendly. It consolidates all operations—including mounting, file locking, and data transfer—into a single TCP connection on port 2049. Therefore, an environment exclusively using NFSv4 mounts does not inherently require rpcbind to be running to maintain storage operations so this customization is not required

